        },
        {
          "name": "text4",
          "value": "Make abstract drawings by connecting points with the same number along opposite sides of an angle. The numbers may not be needed - if so, feel free to omit them - this will make the finished designs a little less cluttered. You can add variety to these by having your child draw with colors. There are lots of amazing examples of this to be found under the category of String Art on the Internet. This circle drawing was made by moving ahead by one dot on one side of the line segment and ahead by two dots on the other side.",
